OL,3,CBreast surgeon was 'nightmare' to work
OL,4,Cwith, former colleague tells inquest
OL,6,FDr Fletcher said multidisciplinary
OL,7,Fmeetings between NHS colleagues to
OL,8,Fdiscuss the treatment of their
OL,9,Fpatients were "always difficult".
OL,11,FHe said: "(Paterson) always tried to
OL,12,Frun the show. We had a period where he
OL,13,Fwas flooding me with work and I was
OL,14,Fstruggling to cope.
OL,16,F"He was being very demanding and I had
OL,17,Fto make a complaint to management to
OL,18,Ftry and calm the situation because he
OL,19,Fwas sending so much stuff we couldn't
OL,20,Fcope."
