OL,3,CBreast surgeon was 'nightmare' to work
OL,4,Cwith, former colleague tells inquest
OL,6,FDr Fletcher said he initially believed
OL,7,FPaterson was just an "efficient and
OL,8,Fcompetent surgeon" but started to
OL,9,Fbecome concerned with the way he was
OL,10,Fcarrying out mastectomies when he
OL,11,Fdiscovered a tumour on a patient's
OL,12,Fmammogram that Paterson had missed
OL,13,Fwhen operating on them.
OL,15,FHe told the inquest: "There was a
OL,16,Ftumour very high up and he had
OL,17,Fobviously missed it. He had been
OL,18,Farrogant and just done what he wanted
OL,19,Fto do and hadn't looked at the
OL,20,Fmammogram.
